# {{ snake_name }} — Package Quick Start

This folder is a reusable Python package. It contains entities, pipes, and
transforms that can be imported by one or more Kindling apps.

## Develop

```bash
poetry install
poetry run poe test
poetry run poe build
```

## Use From An App

Apps live outside package folders, normally under the repo-level `apps/`
directory:

```bash
kindling app init {{ kebab_name }} --package {{ kebab_name }} --repo-root ../..
cd ../../apps/{{ snake_name }}
kindling app run .
```

## Add More Pipes And Entities

Package layout:

```text
src/{{ snake_name }}/
├── entities/       # DataEntities (schemas and storage mappings)
├── pipes/          # DataPipes (orchestration and routing)
└── transforms/     # Pure transformation logic
```

- Add a new entity: create a class registered with `DataEntities.entity(...)` in `entities/`
- Add a new pipe: create a function decorated with `@DataPipes.pipe` in `pipes/`
- Register new modules from an app's `app.py` → `register_all()`
